HEADWORD: Steadfastness
<hw>Stead"fast*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state of
being steadfast; firmness; fixedness; constancy.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>steadfastness</xex> of your faith.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Col. ii.
5.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To prove her wifehood and her <qex>steadfastness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steadily</ent>⟦br⟧
